					System.out.println("Murlok: murloks have always tended to stick to the cruder weapons, bones and skulls and whatnot. they also are the only creature with their own language");
					System.out.println("Though a murlok can learn magic, they have always tended to stick to the easy ways of doing things, mashing, bashing, and slashing");
					System.out.println("HP + 2 | +2 damage | +2 armor | +5 energy");
					System.out.println("");
					System.out.println("Imps may seem cruel and sadistic, but once you get to know them you learn they're rather playfull, its just that their jokes can be a bit much at times");
					System.out.println("since the beggining of their days, the imps have conjured fireballs and bunnies out of hats. It's only natural that they have quite the nack for it by now");
					System.out.println("HP + 2 | +2 Mdamage | +2 Marmor | +5 mana");
					System.out.println("");
					System.out.println("Bristle: bristles are the shapeshifters of the world, able to turn into all kinds of stuff, they are usually timid folk, but you can always find one around... if you can that is");
					System.out.println("A bristle can change into anything to make itself a bit stronger, or have a bit more magic, all within reasonable limits of itself of course");
